#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:5
msgid "DRM RAS over Generic Netlink"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:7
msgid ""
"The DRM RAS (Reliability, Availability, Serviceability) interface provides a "
"standardized way for GPU/accelerator drivers to expose error counters and "
"other reliability nodes to user space via Generic Netlink. This allows "
"diagnostic tools, monitoring daemons, or test infrastructure to query "
"hardware health in a uniform way across different DRM drivers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:13
msgid "Key Goals:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:15
msgid ""
"Provide a standardized RAS solution for GPU and accelerator drivers, "
"enabling data center monitoring and reliability operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:17
msgid ""
"Implement a single drm-ras Generic Netlink family to meet modern Netlink "
"YAML specifications and centralize all RAS-related communication in one "
"namespace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:19
msgid ""
"Support a basic error counter interface, addressing the immediate, essential "
"monitoring needs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:21
msgid ""
"Offer a flexible, future-proof interface that can be extended to support "
"additional types of RAS data in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:23
msgid ""
"Allow multiple nodes per driver, enabling drivers to register separate nodes "
"for different IP blocks, sub-blocks, or other logical subdivisions as "
"applicable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:28
msgid "Nodes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:30
msgid ""
"Nodes are logical abstractions representing an error type or error source "
"within the device. Currently, only error counter nodes is supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:33
msgid ""
"Drivers are responsible for registering and unregistering nodes via the "
"`drm_ras_node_register()` and `drm_ras_node_unregister()` APIs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:37
msgid "Node Management"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:17
msgid ""
"This module provides the infrastructure to manage RAS (Reliability, "
"Availability, and Serviceability) nodes for DRM drivers. Each DRM driver may "
"register one or more RAS nodes, which represent logical components capable "
"of reporting error counters and other reliability metrics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:23
msgid ""
"The nodes are stored in a global xarray `drm_ras_xa` to allow efficient "
"lookup by ID. Nodes can be registered or unregistered dynamically at runtime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:27
msgid ""
"A Generic Netlink family `drm_ras` exposes two main operations to userspace:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:30
msgid ""
"LIST_NODES: Dump all currently registered RAS nodes. The user receives an "
"array of node IDs, names, and types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:33
msgid ""
"GET_ERROR_COUNTER: Get error counters of a given node. Userspace must "
"provide Node ID, Error ID (Optional for specific counter). Returns all "
"counters of a node if only Node ID is provided or specific error counters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:38
msgid "Node registration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:40
msgid ""
"drm_ras_node_register(): Registers a new node and assigns it a unique ID in "
"the xarray."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:42
msgid ""
"drm_ras_node_unregister(): Removes a previously registered node from the "
"xarray."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:45
msgid "Node type:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:47
msgid "ERROR_COUNTER:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:48
msgid "Currently, only error counters are supported."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:49
msgid ""
"The driver must implement the query_error_counter() callback to provide the "
"name and the value of the error counter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:51
msgid ""
"The driver must provide a error_counter_range.last value informing the last "
"valid error ID."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:53
msgid ""
"The driver can provide a error_counter_range.first value informing the first "
"valid error ID."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:55
msgid ""
"The error counters in the driver doesn't need to be contiguous, but the "
"driver must return -ENOENT to the query_error_counter as an indication that "
"the ID should be skipped and not listed in the netlink API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:59
msgid "Netlink handlers:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:61
msgid ""
"drm_ras_nl_list_nodes_dumpit(): Implements the LIST_NODES operation, "
"iterating over the xarray."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:63
msgid ""
"drm_ras_nl_get_error_counter_dumpit(): Implements the GET_ERROR_COUNTER "
"dumpit operation, fetching all counters from a specific node."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:39: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:65
msgid ""
"drm_ras_nl_get_error_counter_doit(): Implements the GET_ERROR_COUNTER doit "
"operation, fetching a counter value from a specific node."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:82
msgid "Dump all registered RAS nodes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:86
#: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:224 ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:295
msgid "**Parameters**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:88
#: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:226 ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:297
msgid "``struct sk_buff *skb``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:83
#: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:221 ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:292
msgid "Netlink message buffer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:85
#: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:223
msgid "``struct netlink_callback *cb``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:84
#: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:222
msgid "Callback context for multi-part dumps"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:86
#: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:224 ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:295
msgid "**Description**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:85
msgid ""
"Iterates over all registered RAS nodes in the global xarray and appends "
"their attributes (ID, name, type) to the given netlink message buffer. Uses "
"**cb->ctx** to track progress in case the message buffer fills up, allowing "
"multi-part dump support. On buffer overflow, updates the context to resume "
"from the last node on the next invocation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:91
#: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:229 ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:298
msgid "**Return**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:92
msgid ""
"0 if all nodes fit in **skb**, number of bytes added to **skb** if the "
"buffer filled up (requires multi-part continuation), or a negative error "
"code on failure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:220
msgid "Dump all Error Counters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:223
msgid ""
"Iterates over all error counters in a given Node and appends their "
"attributes (ID, name, value) to the given netlink message buffer. Uses **cb-"
">ctx** to track progress in case the message buffer fills up, allowing multi-"
"part dump support. On buffer overflow, updates the context to resume from "
"the last node on the next invocation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:230
msgid ""
"0 if all errors fit in **skb**, number of bytes added to **skb** if the "
"buffer filled up (requires multi-part continuation), or a negative error "
"code on failure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:291
msgid "Query an error counter of an node"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:294
msgid "``struct genl_info *info``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:293
msgid "Generic Netlink info containing attributes of the request"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:294
msgid ""
"Extracts the node ID and error ID from the netlink attributes and retrieves "
"the current value of the corresponding error counter. Sends the result back "
"to the requesting user via the standard Genl reply."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras:41: ../drivers/gpu/drm/drm_ras.c:299
msgid "0 on success, or negative errno on failure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:45
msgid "Generic Netlink Usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:47
msgid ""
"The interface is implemented as a Generic Netlink family named ``drm-ras``. "
"User space tools can:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:50
msgid "List registered nodes with the ``list-nodes`` command."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:51
msgid ""
"List all error counters in an node with the ``get-error-counter`` command "
"with ``node-id`` as a parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:53
msgid ""
"Query specific error counter values with the ``get-error-counter`` command, "
"using both ``node-id`` and ``error-id`` as parameters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:57
msgid "YAML-based Interface"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:59
msgid ""
"The interface is described in a YAML specification ``Documentation/netlink/"
"specs/drm_ras.yaml``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:61
msgid ""
"This YAML is used to auto-generate user space bindings via ``tools/net/ynl/"
"pyynl/ynl_gen_c.py``, and drives the structure of netlink attributes and "
"operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:66
msgid "Usage Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:68
msgid "User space must first enumerate nodes to obtain their IDs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:69
msgid ""
"Node IDs or Node names can be used for all further queries, such as error "
"counters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:70
msgid "Error counters can be queried by either the Error ID or Error name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:71
msgid ""
"Query Parameters should be defined as part of the uAPI to ensure user "
"interface stability."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu/drm-ras.rst:72
msgid ""
"The interface supports future extension by adding new node types and "
"additional attributes."
msgstr ""

